---
name: update-tasks
description: Update tasks.md — add, remove, or reorder tasks without touching completed ones.
---

Configuration:
- SPEC_NAME: 001-initial-setup

Path resolution:
- SPEC_FILE = .specify/specs/{SPEC_NAME}/spec.md
- TASKS_FILE = .specify/specs/{SPEC_NAME}/tasks.md

Mandatory reading order:

1. .github/copilot-instructions.md
2. .specify/memory/constitution.md
3. {SPEC_FILE}
4. {TASKS_FILE}

Change request: <!-- describe what to add, remove, or reorganize in tasks.md -->

Execution rules:

1. NEVER modify or remove completed tasks (- [x]). They are permanent record.
2. Adding tasks: append new (- [ ]) items. Must map to a criterion in spec.md.
3. Removing a pending task: mark as obsolete with reason — never hard-delete.
4. Reordering: only reorder pending tasks. Never move completed ones.
5. Splitting a task: replace with 2-3 smaller ones, add split comment.
6. All new tasks must be atomic — completable in a single focused session.
7. If new tasks are not covered by any criterion in spec.md, flag it first.

Required output:
1. What changed in tasks.md (added / marked obsolete / reordered).
2. Total pending tasks remaining after the update.
3. Whether new tasks are covered by existing criteria in spec.md.
